Bulgaria, a paradise for the EU real estate market
The evolution of the Bulgarian real estate market is spectacular, the attention of all Europe is turned to this little-cited Balkan country in the past.
What, or who bought on this EU market that is always the cheapest but will quickly become expensive?
Analysis of the Bulgarian division of Re/Max.
Currently, in real estate, Bulgaria is undoubtedly the most fashionable destination in Eastern Europe with its ski apartments and cheap seaside houses.
In the mountains, the most popular regions are Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitosa and, by the sea, Albena, the "Golden Sands", the "Sun Coast", the old Sozopol and Nessebar but they are increasingly looking for a building in the area of Kavarna and Balcik as well.
According to analysts of Re/Max Bulgaria, sooner or later, the central region of the country, namely Veliko Tarnovo, Gabrovo, Elena, Triavna, will also arouse the interest of investors and they are also increasing in numbers to buy in the very cheap corner of Ruse.
Sofia, the capital, also offers attractive opportunities, the areas of shops and offices promise the highest amortization rate.
Bulgaria is on track to become one of the most attractive golf paradises in Europe and thus be a priority destination, after the summer and winter seasons, also in the other two seasons of the year.
More vigilant investors are already buying in large numbers, for example in the corner of Bansko.
According to analysts, people buying a building in Bulgaria are at the same time looking to change their life, their way of life.
Most buyers are English but others come from France, Belgium, Spain and more and more Romania.
Investors from Malta and Cyprus are also present. On the Black Sea shore and in the most renowned ski resorts, we traditionally meet a lot of Russian buyers.
Foreign buyers are divided into three groups, says Georgij Jankov, regional director of Re/Max Bulgaria.
People who plan to move in buy renovated buildings, at a price ranging from 50 to 100 thousand euros, or old decayed houses, at a price ranging from 5 to 15 thousand euros, which are then renovated.
The criteria are easy access and communication possibilities, the proximity of a large city, shops and in general that of the local doctor.
The second group includes buyers of secondary residences (since last December, Bulgaria is listed among the top 10 holiday destinations in Germany).
The third group consists of commercial investors who buy in the hope of achieving medium or long-term surplus value.
The price of buildings in the capital is constantly rising due to an increasing demand.
In the European Union, real estate prices are the lowest in Bulgaria. However, in the last 5 years, they have increased by 21 percent each year.
The increase in real estate prices essentially exceeds the increase in wages.
Fodor and the six percent Hungarians
According to Gábor Fodor, Minister of Environment and Water, the meetings of the professionals end on Tuesday, however, on Wednesday, after the official opening, the negotiations of the ministers on the international climate regime after 2012 will continue.
Experts and politicians arriving from 192 countries will discuss the Bali Roadmap to define the efforts to be made after the Kyoto Protocol emission reduction period until 2012.
At the moment, there are lively discussions on this issue between developing countries and developed countries.
The United States also reported that, at the moment, it did not want to discuss exact figures, however, it was prepared to sign an agreement on reducing greenhouse gas emissions by 25 to 40 percent by 2020 compared to 1990 levels.
Another important topic at the conference is whether developed countries are committed, apart from emission reductions, to providing financial and technological assistance to countries in need.
An agreement was also signed on aid to be provided to developing countries.
The aid fund defined by the Kyoto Protocol will be managed by a board of directors composed of 16 members likely within the framework of the United Nations Global Environment Facility (GEF), Piac és Profit (Market and Profit) said in a statement.
Six per cent of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, Gábor Fodor, Minister of Environment and Water, confirms the EU's ambition to maintain its role as a flagship in global efforts to protect the climate and encourage the signing of the new international agreement before 2009.
The minister explained that the EU was committed to reducing capacity by 2020 its greenhouse gas emissions by 20 percent from the level reached in 1990, regardless of the success of the signing of the “post-2012 Agreement”, and it was ready to reduce them by up to 30 percent if other major regions of the world and/or their developing countries were also committed to taking responsibility.
Gábor Fodor recalled that in 1997, the countries signatories to the Kyoto Protocol had aimed at a total reduction of 5.2 per cent and all of the 15 EU members of that time made the commitment by 8 per cent less.
Hungary has pledged to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 6 per cent compared to the level between 1985 and 1987, our country will fulfill its commitment, recalls the press release of the Ministry of Environment.
The stakes are high in Bali because the new long-term international agreement on climate policy must be implemented within two years, otherwise the entry into force of the agreement would certainly be postponed after 2012. In this case, the commitments to reduce below the values provided in the Kyoto Protocol would not be followed by the change in the international system.
The reduction in emissions would be delayed and the increase in the average temperature of the Earth by more than 2 degrees Celsius could no longer be avoided, which, according to scientists, would have extremely serious and irreversible consequences.
The British Army recruits on YouTube
British military units are communicating on the video-sharing site recordings made during its operations in Iraq and Afghanistan with the aim of becoming popular.
First, it was the British Air Force (RAF) that became passionate about YouTube: special units intervening in Afghanistan uploaded video footage of operations against the Taliban since March 2006, the BBC announced.
These recordings, taken using miniature cameras mounted on the helmet, are controlled at the Air Force Operations Headquarters in Kandahar and then transferred to London where compatriots upload them to the Internet.
The political message is unavoidable.
The air force soldiers have already passed 139 sequences on the net through this path and their "chain" was watched by more than 75 thousand people.
The U.K. Department of Defense signed up as "defence headquarters" in the spring of 2007 and is communicating videos about operations in Iraq and Afghanistan while the Commonwealth Office and the International Peacekeeping Forces in Iraq (MNFI) also have their own YouTube channels.
Mission in Afghanistan
According to the initial objective of the air force, the videos were posted online to recruit, and according to the Ministry of Defense, they were also used to make the real objectives of the army's presence abroad known to the general public.
The propaganda published through this channel costs practically nothing compared to the usual recruitment advertisements on television, as reported to the BBC Gordon Mackenzie, a defense consultant, but it also inevitably conveys a political message since it justifies in a special form the well-founded military operations decided by the government.
The Americans made a game.
The army is annoyed because, apart from carefully composed and censored videos, amateur videos have been passed on the sharing site that also feature, for example, the death of soldiers: in "official" propaganda films, somewhat hypocritical, officers do not avoid talking about losses but they never present the bloody side.
In fact, many videos had already been posted on the net showing the areas of operations in Iraq and Afghanistan that were being carried out in real mission, but the British military has only recently packed up for loading these videos.
The Americans do the recruiting a little differently by using the free downloadable America's Army shooting game. In this game the player can put himself directly in the place of the soldiers as part of a more or less real simulation.
