That you missed an appointment?
At best, he is sorry and tries to fix things by calling the marketing service to tell them that he forgot to pass the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, it is arranged with excuses.
Before having painful explanations, it’s helpful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make an effort to avoid them.
Are you borrowing something that doesn’t belong to you?
There’s nothing more annoying than wanting to take a file, an office tool or the phone and you can’t find them anywhere.
Do you remember the other day you put the stapler on the desk but it disappeared the next morning?
Do you happen to find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Do not take anything from your colleagues without asking otherwise they are right to be angry with you for having pissed off their property.
