Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which came into force on November 1
In addition to its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of Congress on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the end of the year.
Representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by MEPs and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of agencies for markets to function effectively.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Markets Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the executives of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial advisory services for both specialised social and legal reasons, and creates a new type of financial services (ESI), financial advisory companies (FSAs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it is increasing the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to the regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems, which face competition from current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms, and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they perform, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
Passing through the Congressional Economic Commission, several amendments have been added, including one that highlights that the securitized debts will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has proven itself with what happened with the US high-risk mortgage debt (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the transposition of the management used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after 1977, the Royal Decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists was approved.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the Ombudsman, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require CNMV authorization, and who will be able to provide its product marketing and customer attraction services to different investment firms at the same time.
