What insurance do I need?
Auto insurance, which covers the driver in the event of an accident, involves significant expenses that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, age, age of the driver's license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured, or the use that is made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors such as age, sex, age of the driver's license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the odds to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate than their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
Increasing the frequency increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when determining the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various inconveniences when entering into a contract with affordable insurance, such as poor driving experience and the age of the driver's license.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is full-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most foreseeable drivers can opt for an all-risk insurance with franchise, so that they get coverage from an all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the damage.
"The part of the amount of the damage that the customer pays will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be the higher the amount will be low," said Luis Noguera, Spain's head of First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by for those caused on their own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be cautious and avoid damages as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic fare the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
“Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the profits of the company.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," Noguera clarifies.
After the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to pass a contract with insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
This is why it is best to choose an all-risk insurance with frankness.
"Normally, young people cannot take advantage of the experience previously gained after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at all risks, as long as his financial situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claim rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with a franchise (which can be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed driving and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a larger amount of franchises," said Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, a full-risk insurance with a franchise is preferable (being 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us the most according to our personal situation.
